table_caption: Correlations between FA values and clinical scores.
table_foot: Spearman’s correlations between FA value and age; EDSS and USP-OAB sub-score were tested in HCs and pwMS. EDSS: Expanded Disability Status Scale; FA: fractional anisotropy; MS: multiple sclerosis; N/A: not applicable; p: p-value of correlation; pwMS: patients with MS; r: Spearman’s correlation coefficient (two-tailed); USP-OAB: Urinary Symptom Profile OAB sub-score. *: p < 0.05; **: p < 0.01.
